Actress Bisola Aiyeola has lamented the overwhelming effect of living an independent life. She said she has to get married soonest as she is tired of independent life. The reality TV star, who rose to fame after emerging the first runner up of Big Brother Naija “See Gobe” Season 2 edition, was sharing her opinion on marriage during “Blackbox Roundtable Conversations” with Ebuka Obi-Uchendu. The host on the recent episode tagged: “The ‘IT’ Girls of BBNaija” Part 1, had Tacha, Ceec, Alex Unusual, Mercy Eke, Bisola, Tboss, Dorathy and Erica as guests.   Sekinat’s Idamu Adugbo makes waves     Teddy A: BBNaija not for you if…     Why I’m not involved in politics, by Burna Boy   The guests who are considered some of the biggest stars to ever come out of the BBNaija house, for the first time ever, were brought together to speak about life after the show. They discussed the wins, managing fame and success and the reality of life after Big Brother. While baring her view on marriage, Aiyeola begged Me Right to find her soon. She said she wants to get married before she is 38. “Baby please find me, I’m single and tired of being Independent I want to be dependent. “I’ve been independent since I was 17years. I’m 36 now I want to be married so I can give birth to another child before 38 oh,” she said.